The paper deals with game theory and the existence of pure Nash equilibria, which are central topics in the field of computational game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the practical applications of weakly acyclic games, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper uses mathematical proofs and analysis to establish the link between subgame equilibria and weak acyclicity, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the distributed dynamics of better-response moves, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI).
